## Phase Summaries

**Phases 1-8** established the core game: coin economy, overgrowth difficulty, airplane flyovers, near-miss/objectives/jackpot juice, production hardening, branding, micro-polish, player experience (daily modifiers, vehicle unlocks, sound enrichment), and store readiness.

**Phases 9-15** polished the experience: specials overhaul (9 power-ups), audio/visuals, scoring cleanup, HUD redesign, game logic audit, UX truth pass, popup/branding style parity.

**Phase 16** — Encounter discovery: helicopter and train design memos.

**Phase 17** — Police helicopter: `PoliceChaseState.variant` ('car' | 'helicopter'). Helicopter spawns from chase #3+. Airborne movement (ignores obstacles/ice), helicopter sprite with spinning rotor, police body flash, and searchlight. Rotor chop audio replacing siren. Amber "CHOPPER" edge warning.

**Phase 18** — Train encounter: train spawns at viewport center with random horizontal/vertical axis. Caltrain-style multi-car sprite. Train horn + crossing rumble audio. Yellow "TRAIN" edge warning. "HIT BY TRAIN" game over. Ghost immunity. Encounter stagger with police/plane. Max 1 per run, after 30s.

**Phase 19** — Branding: horizontal stepped color band backgrounds (dark navy → teal) across all SVGs. PNGs regenerated.

**Phase 20** — Gameplay audit (research-informed): audited the full game loop against Mike Stout telegraphing, MDA framework, and Vlambeer game-feel principles. Telegraphing hierarchy (1.5s train > 1.1s police/chopper > 0.9s plane) confirmed fair with readable pre-cues; difficulty escalates through route pressure, not hidden state. Economy pacing validated: coin spawns, police ramp, plane drops, and train timing all satisfying across 30-90s runs. Game feel improvements: punchier coin burst particles (5-8 count, radius 2.5, 280-380ms lifetime), new near-miss orange flash particles, buffed drift sparks (3-4 count, 200ms lifetime), extended near-miss toast TTL from 600ms to 800ms.

**Phase 21** — Sprite & visual consistency pass: audited all sprite files across player vehicles, encounters, pickups, and overgrowth. Fixed buggy missing `drawContourOutline` keyline (coupe and truck already had it). All encounter sprites (police, helicopter, plane, train) confirmed visually consistent. Coin, special pickup shapes, and overgrowth stages all well-designed and readable.

**Phase 22** — Popup, manifest & marketplace review: added missing Nitro boost (Space) control to popup.html controls table. All 9 power-up tags verified accurate. Manifest description (102 chars) within ≤132 limit. All icon sizes (16/32/48/128) present. Store cover (1280×800) and tile (440×280) SVGs confirmed. README gameplay section cross-checked. INSTALL-FOR-FRIENDS.md already up to date.

**Phase 23** — Debug screen (sprite showcase) polish: added VEHICLES, ENCOUNTERS, PICKUPS section labels to the showcase. All sprites, edge warnings (police/chopper/plane/train), sound test buttons with active states, and train positioning verified. Theme cycling (arrow keys) and enter/exit restore confirmed clean.

**Phase 24** — HUD text fitting & layout: abbreviated "EARLY OVERGROWTH" → "EARLY GROWTH" to fit info panel, added clip region to info block for overflow safety. All HUD panels (info, POWER, GOAL, controls hint) verified at narrow/wide viewports with no text clipping or overlap.

**Phase 25** — Code refactoring & production readiness: fixed circular dependency (gameStateTypes → sprites → trainSprite) by extracting ViewportEdge to shared/types. Internalized unused exports (OVERLAY_ROOT_ID, getTrainRect). Zero `as any`, `console.log`, `__domRacerDebug`, `TODO/FIXME`. All 15 config sections verified used. Bundle: 160 KB (44 KB gzip). No dev-only code leaks.

**Phase 26** — Game state collision & edge-case testing: 19 new tests across encounter overlap stress (stagger prevents triple-overlap, ghost dismisses helicopter + prevents train collision), effect interactions (9-effect rapid succession, mystery resolution, dual-effect independence), lifecycle edge cases (rapid restart field resets, comprehensive beginRun audit, multiple rapid beginRun calls), and boundary tests (police edge spawn, small viewport train, score overflow, overgrowth bounds, VFX cleanup). Total: 119 tests across 10 files.

## Post-Phase Polish

After all phases, additional refinements were made:
- Helicopter police lights enhanced (body flash + siren glow)
- Sprite showcase: helicopter, train, and clickable sound test panel with active-state indicators
- "MUSIC" → "SOUND" label fix across HUD and docs
- SLIPPERY daily modifier removed (disorienting); first-play protection added (no modifier on first session)
- First police arrival tuned faster (8-10s instead of 12-15s)
- Unpause grace: 1.5s timer extension when tab regains focus
- Train simplified: spawns at viewport center instead of DOM element detection
- Production readiness audit: dead code removed, unused exports internalized, duplicate clamp fixed

## Phase Closeout Protocol

Every phase ends with a mandatory closeout pass before marking `done`:

1. **Refactor & simplify** — dead code, duplication, naming
2. **Productionize** — no debug artifacts, no `console.log`, no `__domRacerDebug`
3. **Tests** — updated, new coverage, `npm run test` green
4. **Lint & format** — `npm run lint:fix && npm run format`, zero warnings
5. **Build** — `npm run build` succeeds cleanly
6. **Docs** — update SOUL.md, README.md, next-session.mdc, phases.mdc
7. **Commit** — single clean commit summarizing deliverables

